The paper discusses the use of swarm robotics systems in an urban environment for waste management, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of bio-inspired foraging methods and stigmergy-based navigation, which are common techniques in multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the efficiency and autonomy of the proposed system, which are key aspects of control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
